OL,6,FThere is an important question though
OL,7,Fabout the amount of repetition within
OL,8,Fthe bulletins. Each half-hourly
OL,9,Fbulletin can seem very similar in the
OL,10,Fabsence of a developing story.
OL,12,FIt might seem a chore to see the same
OL,13,Fthing twice. The onus should be on the
OL,14,Fpresenter and journalist outputting the
OL,15,Fopts to freshen up scripts as the
OL,16,Fmorning progresses.
OL,18,FIt's thought a typical Breakfast viewer
OL,19,Fsees between 30 and 40 minutes of the
OL,20,Fprogramme so there was a logic in
OL,21,Fdropping one of the bulletins.
OL,3,CBBC regional news resumes pre-pandemic
OL,4,Cschedule at breakfast
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/6
